All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Compressor
    ** THIS CLASS IS ONLY FOR STEP TWO AND THREE** This class is connected to and uses TheDictionary class to help with conversions from and to .cmp and .txt files.
    Driver
    This class kick starts the text editing program, prompting the user whether he or she would like to edit a current file or create a new one.
    DriverStep2
    This class kick starts the program for step 2 and 3.
    Editor
    This class represents the "Editor" that will edit TextFile object, which will later be converted in .txt files in the future.
    EditorStep2
    This class represents the "Editor" that will edit TextFileStep2 object, which will later be converted into either .cmp or .txt files in the future.
    TextFile
    This file represents the text file that will hold lines of text for N+1 many times.
    TextFileStep2
    This class represents a text file that enables users to create and swap between .txt and .cmp files depending on what they ask for.
    TheDictionary
    ** THIS CLASS IS ONLY FOR STEP TWO AND THREE** This class represents the dictionary that is created and specific to each individual file (or TextFileStep2) that is loaded.
    UserScanner
    This class simplifies the process in which the compiler takes in and processes the user input.
    UserScannerStep2
    This class simplifies the process in which the compiler takes in and processes the user input.
    Word
    **THIS CLASS IS FOR STEP TWO AND THREE ONLY** This class represents an individual word that helps the dictionary (stored as a LinkedList in Compressor) remember the numerical of each unique word.
